      {
        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "Notes:\n- These three values are the stepwise macro pKa’s for the triprotic citric acid at 25 °C and I = 0.10 M. In the acid dissociation direction, they correspond to H3L → H2L (pKa1 = 2.90), H2L → HL (pKa2 = 4.35), and HL → L (pKa3 = 5.65).\n- The increasing sequence (2.90 < 4.35 < 5.65) is typical for polyprotic carboxylic acids due to progressively reduced charge stabilization after each deprotonation.",
